{"ts": "2026-06-07T11:50:33.239219+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "**Triage Result: Confirmed Bug — No Write Access to Take Action**\n\n## Issue Analysis\n\n**Issue #1**: `apply_migrations.sh` applies files in wrong order on case-folding filesystems (macOS APFS).\n\n**Root cause confirmed**: The script at [`scripts/apply_migrations.sh`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/blob/main/scripts/apply_migrations.sh) uses:\n\n```bash\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n```\n\nThis relies on the shell's glob expansion ordering, which is **locale-dependent**. On case-insensitive filesystems (macOS APFS) with `LC_COLLATE=en_US.UTF-8`, the collation algorithm can sort `003_add_session_index.sql` ahead of `002_create_sessions.sql`, causing a failure because the index in `003` depends on the `sessions` table created in `002`.\n\n**Evidence**:\n- `migrations/001_create_users.sql` — creates `users` table\n- `migrations/002_create_sessions.sql` — creates `sessions` table (depends on `001`)\n- `migrations/003_add_session_index.sql` — creates index on `sessions.user_id` (depends on `002`)\n\nThe three files have strict ordering dependencies, but the glob-based loop doesn't guarantee that order across all platforms/locales.\n\n**Suggested fix** (2 options, both more robust than `ls | sort`):\n\nOption 1 — `find` with `sort`:\n```bash\nwhile IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone < <(find migrations/ -name '*.sql' -type f | sort)\n```\n\nOption 2 — explicit sort with `C` locale:\n```bash\nfor f in $(printf '%s\\n' migrations/*.sql | LC_ALL=C sort); do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\n**Action taken**: Attempted to comment and add a `bug` label, but the personal access token lacks write permissions to this repository (403 on both operations). The issue is valid, well-reported, and ready for a PR fix. The reporter (@BruceKZ) offered to send a PR, which would be the ideal next step.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 568, "prompt_tokens": 10742, "total_tokens": 11310, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 32, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10624}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10624, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 118}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "28946829-f7a3-4674-a298-e8e0e47811c2", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea1eb-86e8-78c2-92c0-d1c7f649846f-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10742, "output_tokens": 568, "total_tokens": 11310, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10624}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 32}}}}]}}}
{"kind": "token_usage", "ts": "2026-06-07T11:50:33.239552+00:00", "usage": {"input_tokens": 65145, "output_tokens": 3059, "total_tokens": 68204, "calls": 9}}
